In practice, you use Chef to manage your servers remotely, typically from a Linux, Mac OS, or Windows workstation. But for learning purposes, you'll start by managing a server directly to get a feel for how Chef works.

Because you'll directly modify the state of your machine, we strongly suggest that you work through this topic in a disposable environment such as an Ubuntu virtual machine. We'll provide you with an environment in the first step.
